    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p><i>11th-level artificer feature</i></p><p>You can now store a spell in an object. Whenever you finish a long rest, you can touch one <a href=\"https://2014.5e.tools/items.html#blankhash,flstsource:phb=1,flstcategory:basic=1,flsttype:martial%20weapon=1~simple%20weapon=1\">simple or martial weapon</a> or one item that you can use as a spellcasting focus, and you store a spell in it, choosing a 1st- or 2nd-level spell from the <a href=\"https://2014.5e.tools/spells.html#blankhash,flstclass:artificer=1,flstcast%20time:action=1,flstlevel:1=1~2=1\">artificer spell list</a> that requires 1 action to cast (you needn't have it prepared).</p><p>While holding the object, a creature can take an action to produce the spell's effect from it, using your spellcasting ability modifier. If the spell requires @status[concentration], the creature must concentrate. The spell stays in the object until it's been used a number of times equal to twice your Intelligence modifier (minimum of twice) or until you use this feature again to store a spell in an object.</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
